<p>The second step is mounting the terminal in the selected position. The mount should be secure, serviceable, and safe. The terminal should not be placed where people can knock it, where drainage water can hit it, or where maintenance teams will step on the cable. The cable route should be neat, protected, and sealed where it enters the building.</p>

<p>The third step is router setup and testing. The installer should connect the indoor equipment, create a secure Wi-Fi name and password, activate or configure the service where required, and test performance. Testing should include download speed, upload speed, latency, and real applications such as video calls, browsing, cloud tools, payment systems, CCTV remote view, or streaming. For latency-specific planning, see <a href="/amazon-leo-internet-latency-in-kenya">Amazon LEO Internet latency in Kenya</a>.</p>

